Day 14:
Step 0: Log in to the Azure Portal (https://portal.azure.com/).


_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


1. Azure Table Storage:
Step 1: Create a new Resource Group:

--> Create a Storage Account:
Step 1: You can search STORAGE ACCOUNTS in Search bar.
Step 2: Enter the necessary details: 
        a. Storage Accounts name
        b. Performance - Standard
        c. Region
        d. Performance
        e. Access Tier - hot
Step 3: Then click on CREATE when you go to review+create.
Step 4: Once depolyment is complete, go to resource group to view your Storage Account.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 2: Click on Table which is located in the overview of Storage Account.
Step 3: Enter the necessary details: 
        a.Table name
Step 4: In Table, you can add entities.
Step 5: Create a LOGIC APPS.

--> Steps to create LOGIC APP:
Step 1: You can search LOGIC APP in Search bar.
Step 2: Enter the necessary details: 
        a. Logic App name
        b. Subscription
        c. Region
Step 3: Then click on CREATE when you go to review + create.
Step 4: Once depolyment is complete, go to resource group to view your Logic App.
Step 4: Go to Logic App Designer and click on add trigger to add the following in your logic app:
      a. Schedule
      b. Azure Table
Step 5: Then for testing click on RUN in Logic App's Overview page.


